I​ hate to give this 2 stars. The content is really good. The instructor is solid and easy to understand. It does rely a bit too much on outside reading. The real killer is the peer review at the end. I waited almost 48 hours for my class to get reviewed... I do like to power through classes, because then you can get them for free. Forcing the classes to take nearly 48 hours longer than it took me to complete just to get someone to review my final little project isn't a morally acceptable business model. I'm nearly done with the final phase of this full course, but I will absolutely be canceling the subscription prior to 7 days if all I'm doing is waiting for someone to review it. I'd say it's 100% worth the $40... but the principle is ugly.
